result.execSummary:
The defendant Andrew C Eltrevoog was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Entitled Amended Criminal Complaint:  Count 1 - Misdemeanor Battery and Count 2 - Disorderly Conduct, Domestic Abuse

10:40  Defendant Andrew C Eltrevoog in court with attorney William Ginsberg.  Jane E. Kohlwey appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Amended Criminal Complaint (Amended Information) filed; defendant pled No Contest to Cts 1 & 2 in Amended Criminal Complaint; Court found defendant guilty and ordered JOC.  Victim made no statement.  Sentence withheld and defendant placed on probation for two years w/conds: anger management counselling, parenting classes, not possess or consume alcohol, and maintain absolute sobriety; fine & costs on Ct. 1 of $443 and on Ct. 2 of $543; 2 days jail credit.  11:00
